Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
items.location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

items.summary: Unity Ride in honor of Alex Pretti
items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Unity Ride in honor of Alex Pretti Instagram. 

When: Saturday Jan 31, 2026 1:00 PM. Meet at 1 pm, roll at 1:30 pm.

Start: Washburn Fair Oaks (park across from MIA, 24th St and 3rd Ave S) 

Finish: VA Medical Center-Minneapolis

Distance: ~9 miles (one-way route) Pace: Slow roll, no-drop

“Alex was one of us, could’ve been any of us, so as we mourn, all of us can come together in unity to remember Alex for what he was. A kind and caring soul put on this earth to be the light for others. Although his light has been extinguished by this fascist regime, it hasn’t been lost. If anything, those sparks fell and ignited something in us that’s been hiding all along. We are stronger together, and they can’t take us all. We’ve gathered together a community of cyclists to remember Alex Pretti. Please join in, near or far this Saturday, 1/31 1:00 PM Central Time


Minneapolis joins together Angry Catfish Bicycle, Bonesaw Cycling Collective, GenoSack, Melanin In Motion, The Price Brothers, Unsanctioned Ride group and others. We hope folks from all over join together in unity as well!”


Route will travel to Alex’s memorial, then to Renee’s, and end at the VA medical center near Ford Bridge.
items.location: Washburn Fair Oaks, 200 E 24th St, Minneapolis, MN 55404, USA
